1
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:15,767
I've already booked your ticket.

2
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:17,033
Everything is set.

3
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,233
You're leaving in two days.

4
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:20,833
In two days?

5
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:22,833
Why do we have to delay it?

6
00:00:22,900 --> 00:00:24,300
Red needs to know about this.

7
00:00:24,367 --> 00:00:25,967
You can't do this alone.

8
00:00:26,033 --> 00:00:28,467
Raichu, what about my mom?

9
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:30,300
Why aren't you touching
your food?

10
00:00:30,367 --> 00:00:32,033
I don't feel like eating.

11
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:33,867
Your aunt told me
it's your favorite food.

12
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:35,967
That's fried chicken.

13
00:00:36,033 --> 00:00:37,667
I'm going to get some rest.

14
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:39,533
I ordered a cochinillo.

15
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,900
It's Red's favorite. I'm sure
he's going to love it.

16
00:00:41,967 --> 00:00:44,100
You're so sweet.

17
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:45,333
Probably that's why
you convinced him

18
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:46,800
to go back to the States.

19
00:00:46,867 --> 00:00:48,867
He has to.

20
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:54,633
Eden might find a way to seduce
him if he stays here.

21
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:55,800
Gold digger!

22
00:00:55,867 --> 00:00:57,600
Why do you have
Red's belongings?

23
00:00:57,667 --> 00:00:59,033
He asked me to get it for him.

24
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,367
Why? What's going on?

25
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:02,667
Didn't you and Eden know?

26
00:01:02,733 --> 00:01:04,600
He's leaving today for the US.

27
00:01:04,667 --> 00:01:05,767
He's staying there for good.

28
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:07,600
I'm going to meet with Red.

29
00:01:07,700 --> 00:01:09,567
I'm going to tell him
I'm pregnant.

30
00:01:09,633 --> 00:01:10,533
Eden!
He's leaving!

31
00:01:11,567 --> 00:01:13,233
Today is his flight to the US!

32
00:01:13,300 --> 00:01:14,567
He'll be staying there for good.

33
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:15,767
What?

34
00:01:15,833 --> 00:01:17,767
Red, there's something
you need to know.

35
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:19,700
I know you're going
to the States.

36
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:21,267
I don't want to stop you
from leaving, but...

37
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:22,567
I'm going to be a father?

38
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:23,633
Red, let's go.

39
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:24,667
You're going to miss
your flight.

40
00:01:24,733 --> 00:01:25,667
Come on.

41
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,400
Red!

42
00:01:28,467 --> 00:01:29,867
Come on, get in the car!

43
00:01:29,933 --> 00:01:30,967
- Get inside!
- Raichu!

44
00:01:59,033 --> 00:02:00,367
Red, where are we?

45
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:04,367
We're in Punta Miguel.

46
00:02:05,767 --> 00:02:08,533
Let's stay here while we're
still figuring out what to do.

47
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:10,767
I'm sorry.

48
00:02:11,867 --> 00:02:13,133
I panicked.

49
00:02:15,267 --> 00:02:16,267
I don't know what to do.

50
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:18,733
All I thought about is
to get away from them.

51
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,533
Because if I don't,
they'll send me to the States.

52
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,167
I can't leave you.

53
00:02:23,233 --> 00:02:24,900
Red, until when are we going
to stay here?

54
00:02:25,967 --> 00:02:29,100
We need to face our parents
and ask them for forgiveness.

55
00:02:30,367 --> 00:02:32,867
Of course, we'll face them.

56
00:02:34,033 --> 00:02:36,133
We just need time to think.

57
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,633
We need to figure out a way
to tell them

58
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:39,333
without making them so upset.

59
00:02:52,833 --> 00:02:54,233
Dindi.

60
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:55,167
Yes?

61
00:02:55,233 --> 00:02:56,200
Is this yours?

62
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,333
Pregnancy test?

63
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,667
I don't even have a boyfriend.

64
00:03:00,733 --> 00:03:02,333
I'm not delusional.

65
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:05,433
If it's not yours...

66
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:08,533
then whose is it?

67
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,800
I found this in our garbage.

68
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:25,667
Yen?

69
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:32,767
Amanda, what's wrong?

70
00:03:36,433 --> 00:03:37,400
Amanda.

71
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,200
Where are you going?

72
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:46,700
I'm going to be a father.

73
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:48,833
Do you regret it?

74
00:03:50,167 --> 00:03:52,900
No, of course not.

75
00:03:52,967 --> 00:03:54,667
Yen, I don't regret anything.

76
00:03:56,033 --> 00:03:57,133
Because I love you.

77
00:03:58,433 --> 00:04:01,900
I'm just wondering

78
00:04:01,967 --> 00:04:05,933
if I'm capable of handling
this huge responsibility.

79
00:04:08,133 --> 00:04:10,400
I just have a lot
on my mind right now.

80
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:15,367
I feel the same.

81
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:18,367
I feel bad for our baby

82
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:20,800
because he'll get dragged
into this mess.

83
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,300
Yen...

84
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:30,767
that's why we need
to help each other out.

85
00:04:31,867 --> 00:04:35,800
We now have more reason to fight
for our relationship.

86
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:40,433
I feel like I'm drowning
already.

87
00:04:41,633 --> 00:04:42,733
We can do this.

88
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:50,133
We went through a more difficult
situation on the island.

89
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,800
But we got through it all.

90
00:04:52,867 --> 00:04:55,667
Just keep in mind
that we're a tandem. Okay?

91
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:58,067
We're partners. We'll help
each other out.

92
00:04:58,133 --> 00:05:00,767
No one will be left behind,
and no one will give up. Okay?

93
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,567
It's Raichu.

94
00:05:13,533 --> 00:05:14,633
Hello, Raichu!

95
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:16,033
Hello, Eden!

96
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:17,167
Where are you?

97
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:19,300
I'm getting worried.

98
00:05:19,367 --> 00:05:21,367
Red and I had to get away.

99
00:05:23,567 --> 00:05:25,833
His uncle might force him
to go to the airport.

100
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:28,833
So we came here to Punta Verde.

101
00:05:29,867 --> 00:05:31,733
I can breathe easily now.

102
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:34,033
I'm happy for you.

103
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:35,367
Thank you.

104
00:05:35,467 --> 00:05:38,100
If it wasn't for you, Red and I
wouldn't be together right now.

105
00:05:38,167 --> 00:05:42,433
You know that I'm happy
when you're happy.

106
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:45,333
But I hope Red has a plan
for both of you.

107
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,200
What about your parents?

108
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:51,533
Of course, we'll be going back
to Manila.

109
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,567
We need to apologize to them.

110
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:55,833
Okay.

111
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,267
Things will get better.

112
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:58,300
Let's claim it.

113
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:05,800
Are you sure
this is the right way?

114
00:06:05,867 --> 00:06:08,067
Is your GPS working fine?

115
00:06:08,167 --> 00:06:09,100
Yes, it's working fine.

116
00:06:10,367 --> 00:06:13,100
Zandro, can you drive faster?
You're so slow!

117
00:06:13,167 --> 00:06:14,300
Drive faster.

118
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:18,233
Rina, we might get in an
accident if I drive faster.

119
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,467
You will get in an accident
for sure!

120
00:06:19,533 --> 00:06:21,700
Because I'm going to smack you!

121
00:06:21,767 --> 00:06:23,833
You're always stressing me out!

122
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:25,100
Rina, knock it off.

123
00:06:25,167 --> 00:06:27,700
It has already happened. We
can't do anything about it now.

124
00:06:27,767 --> 00:06:30,000
I don't want Red to get married.

125
00:06:30,067 --> 00:06:33,633
And I don't want Eden
to become my daughter-in-law.

126
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:35,000
So what now?

127
00:06:35,067 --> 00:06:36,600
Amanda is going to be
my son's mother-in-law?

128
00:06:36,667 --> 00:06:37,967
Please, no!

129
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:44,367
Amanda, what's going on?

130
00:06:44,433 --> 00:06:47,667
I can't contact Eden.

131
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:48,767
Eden?

132
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:50,767
Why? Was it Eden who used that
pregnancy test?

133
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:52,767
Amanda!

134
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:54,400
What's going on?

135
00:06:54,467 --> 00:06:55,433
Hello?

136
00:06:56,467 --> 00:06:57,467
Raichu?

137
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:02,000
I think I lost the signal.

138
00:07:02,067 --> 00:07:02,967
Hello?

139
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:04,200
Hello, Eden?

140
00:07:04,267 --> 00:07:05,233
Eden?

141
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:08,033
- Eden? Hello.
- Where is my daughter?

142
00:07:15,167 --> 00:07:16,767
Where is Eden?

143
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,600
Please, tell me where she is.

144
00:07:20,133 --> 00:07:22,000
Raichu, don't lie to us.

145
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:23,033
Where is Eden?

146
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:23,933
Where did she go?

147
00:07:26,267 --> 00:07:27,800
I'm sorry.

148
00:07:27,867 --> 00:07:29,200
She eloped with Red.

149
00:07:48,633 --> 00:07:50,067
I wish we could be like this
all the time.

150
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,300
We're at peace.

151
00:07:55,167 --> 00:07:56,700
No one's yelling at each other.

152
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,500
It feels like
we're back on the island.

153
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:04,433
You're right.

154
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:06,367
It won't be good for the baby.

155
00:08:07,667 --> 00:08:10,633
She needs to be
in a good environment.

156
00:08:12,233 --> 00:08:13,267
You know what?

157
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:14,933
What?

158
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:18,000
I want our baby
to be full of love.

159
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,967
Speaking of full.

160
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:24,967
Aren't you hungry? They say
pregnant women love to eat.

161
00:08:26,233 --> 00:08:27,733
I think it's kind of true.

162
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,500
I knew it.

163
00:08:29,567 --> 00:08:32,233
Wait here. I'm going to get us
some food.

164
00:08:32,300 --> 00:08:33,933
- Stay here.
- Okay.

165
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,500
I need to take good care of you.

166
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:38,333
Because there are two of you
now.

167
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,700
- You're funny.
- Wait here.

168
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:51,733
Rina, we're here.

169
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,900
I wonder if Red is here.

170
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:00,933
Hello?

171
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:01,967
Raichu!

172
00:09:03,867 --> 00:09:05,267
What? I can't understand you.

173
00:09:06,267 --> 00:09:08,567
You must have a poor signal.

174
00:09:08,633 --> 00:09:10,167
Wait, I'll look
for better reception.

175
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:13,533
Hello?

176
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:17,700
Raichu?

177
00:09:19,667 --> 00:09:20,600
Raichu, hold on.

178
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:22,067
I'll look for a better signal.

179
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:26,900
Hello?

180
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:27,933
Raichu.

181
00:09:32,333 --> 00:09:34,767
I'm going to get him arrested.

182
00:09:34,833 --> 00:09:37,833
He can't take Eden away
just like that.

183
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:41,967
What if Eden went with him
out of her own will?

184
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:46,267
That's not possible.

185
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:48,867
She told me she'd broken up
with him already.

186
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:53,000
She promised me
she'd let Red go.

187
00:09:54,433 --> 00:09:55,633
Unless she's...

188
00:09:57,067 --> 00:09:58,067
What?

189
00:09:59,367 --> 00:10:00,400
Unless she's what?

190
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:03,233
That the pregnancy kit
is Eden's?

191
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:05,033
No! That's not true.

192
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:07,133
Don't say that.
I don't want to think it's true.

193
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,100
Why don't you just talk
to his parents?

194
00:10:09,167 --> 00:10:10,200
You guys are the parents.

195
00:10:10,267 --> 00:10:11,600
You should fix the problem.

196
00:10:11,667 --> 00:10:13,900
Do you think we can talk
some sense into Rina?

197
00:10:15,733 --> 00:10:19,400
We're messing
with the kids' life.

198
00:10:19,467 --> 00:10:22,000
We should let them make
a decision for themselves.

199
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:23,200
They're old enough.

200
00:10:23,267 --> 00:10:25,500
Should I let my daughter
have Rina as her mother-in-law?

201
00:10:25,567 --> 00:10:29,300
No way! I will do everything
to get Eden back.

202
00:10:36,533 --> 00:10:38,500
Hello?

203
00:10:38,567 --> 00:10:40,400
Raichu, I can't hear you.

204
00:10:46,633 --> 00:10:48,233
Hello?

205
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:50,667
You have a poor signal.

206
00:10:51,733 --> 00:10:53,767
How are you, Eden?

207
00:10:56,167 --> 00:11:00,700
Did you think you could get away
from us?

208
00:11:00,767 --> 00:11:03,900
I can find you
even if you hide in hell.

209
00:11:05,367 --> 00:11:06,367
Gold digger!

210
00:11:08,033 --> 00:11:11,633
Why are you forcing yourself
on my son?

211
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:13,533
Is that what your mom
taught you?

212
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,967
Your opportunist mom!

213
00:11:16,033 --> 00:11:17,767
That's not true.

214
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:19,600
I love Red.

215
00:11:19,667 --> 00:11:21,700
Liar! You're such a liar!

216
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:24,967
Your mom told you
that we're rich.

217
00:11:25,033 --> 00:11:28,133
That's why you're pushing
yourself to my son!

218
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:32,667
I never look at people's wealth.

219
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:35,033
Don't give me that crap!

220
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:37,567
I won't believe
your fake innocence.

221
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:40,500
Because of you,

222
00:11:40,567 --> 00:11:42,733
my son missed his flight
to the States!

223
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:47,467
You ruined all our plans
for him!

224
00:11:47,533 --> 00:11:49,500
You ruined my son's life!

225
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:53,333
So now,

226
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,933
I'm going to destroy your face!

227
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,367
Let's see if he'll still
like you after this!

228
00:11:57,433 --> 00:11:58,900
- Mom!
- You beast!

229
00:11:58,967 --> 00:12:00,533
You can't hurt her!

230
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:08,033
And why not?

231
00:12:09,167 --> 00:12:11,400
She's the reason
you fooled your dad and me.

232
00:12:11,467 --> 00:12:13,200
You were on your way
to the States!

233
00:12:13,267 --> 00:12:14,900
Why did you have to meet
with that woman?

234
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,633
And you ran away with her again!

235
00:12:18,167 --> 00:12:19,800
What does that woman have?

236
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:23,133
Why can't you leave her?

237
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:25,833
You're choosing that woman
over your dad and me!

238
00:12:44,233 --> 00:12:45,200
Eden!

239
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,167
Mom.

240
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,533
Mom, I'm sorry.

241
00:12:52,167 --> 00:12:53,467
I'm sorry, Mom.

242
00:12:55,067 --> 00:12:57,467
Red, come home.

243
00:12:57,533 --> 00:12:59,867
Eden brings you nothing
but trouble.

244
00:13:00,933 --> 00:13:02,167
Leave her.

245
00:13:02,233 --> 00:13:04,167
I can't leave her.

246
00:13:05,567 --> 00:13:06,533
Why?

247
00:13:10,067 --> 00:13:11,233
You're a liar!

248
00:13:13,033 --> 00:13:16,333
You told me you'd break up
with that guy!

249
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:18,133
So why did you elope with him?

250
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:20,000
Why?

251
00:13:20,067 --> 00:13:22,333
Mom, I'm sorry.

252
00:13:22,433 --> 00:13:24,233
I'm sorry.

253
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:25,333
You're sorry?

254
00:13:26,367 --> 00:13:27,300
You're apologizing again.

255
00:13:27,367 --> 00:13:28,633
Is that all you can do?

256
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:32,400
Say sorry? But you keep doing
the same thing over and over.

257
00:13:42,633 --> 00:13:43,900
My baby.

258
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:46,833
What did you say?

259
00:13:49,667 --> 00:13:51,367
What did you just say?

260
00:13:51,433 --> 00:13:53,400
Mom, forgive me.

261
00:13:55,833 --> 00:13:56,833
Amanda!

262
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:57,867
Eden!

263
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:03,533
Eden is pregnant?

264
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:07,567
No, you're not serious.

265
00:14:09,467 --> 00:14:12,167
You heard that right, Mom, Dad.

266
00:14:12,233 --> 00:14:16,433
And that's a valid reason
I can't go to the States.

267
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,333
I'm going to take responsibility
for her.

268
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:20,167
No.

269
00:14:20,233 --> 00:14:24,167
That criminal's daughter
can never be part of our family!

270
00:14:24,233 --> 00:14:27,567
Well, sorry. I'm not asking
permission from you.

271
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:29,733
I'm just telling you my plans...

272
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:30,900
what I'm about to do.

273
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:34,467
I won't abandon my child.

274
00:14:34,533 --> 00:14:35,767
Your grandchild.

275
00:14:37,233 --> 00:14:39,167
I came here...

276
00:14:40,833 --> 00:14:43,200
because Red needs to know
the truth.

277
00:14:44,567 --> 00:14:45,967
What does he need to know?

278
00:14:50,267 --> 00:14:52,933
I hope my suspicions are wrong.

279
00:14:58,367 --> 00:14:59,300
Mom.

280
00:14:59,367 --> 00:15:00,333
Tell me.

281
00:15:03,233 --> 00:15:04,767
Mom, I'm pregnant.

282
00:15:07,167 --> 00:15:12,667
And Red is the father of my
baby.

283
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:14,667
Mom, I didn't mean to hurt you.

284
00:15:14,733 --> 00:15:16,767
I didn't mean to do this to you.

285
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:18,400
I didn't expect this to happen.

286
00:15:18,467 --> 00:15:19,600
Don't touch me!

287
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:21,267
- Don't come near me!
- Amanda!

288
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:22,600
Don't come near me!

289
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:23,633
Eden!

290
00:15:36,233 --> 00:15:37,467
Mom...

291
00:15:37,533 --> 00:15:40,067
please, forgive me.

292
00:15:40,133 --> 00:15:42,633
I didn't mean to hurt you.

293
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,767
Please, forgive me.

294
00:15:48,167 --> 00:15:49,667
Mom.

295
00:15:49,733 --> 00:15:50,700
Mom, please.

296
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:55,400
I don't want to hurt you.

297
00:15:55,467 --> 00:15:58,900
But you keep hurting me
over and over.

298
00:16:01,933 --> 00:16:04,433
I don't know what to tell you.

299
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:08,233
I don't know what to do with you
anymore!

300
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:10,367
Mom...

301
00:16:12,167 --> 00:16:15,267
I still haven't gotten over
what you did,

302
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:17,000
and here you go again!

303
00:16:19,733 --> 00:16:21,933
How many times are you going
to hurt me?

304
00:16:23,033 --> 00:16:24,533
How many times are you going
to hurt me?

305
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,067
How many times?

306
00:16:26,133 --> 00:16:28,767
Tell me! So I'll know!

307
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:32,533
So I'll know if I still have
the strength to bear the pain!

308
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:35,500
Because I've already spent
all my strength!

309
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:38,800
I can't believe
what I'm hearing.

310
00:16:38,867 --> 00:16:40,133
What about your future?

311
00:16:42,533 --> 00:16:44,267
You can't do anything now.

312
00:16:44,333 --> 00:16:48,000
I am old enough
to make decisions for myself.

313
00:16:48,067 --> 00:16:51,100
And I will do
what I think is right.

314
00:16:51,167 --> 00:16:53,300
Whether you like it or not.

315
00:16:53,367 --> 00:16:54,700
Red! Red!

316
00:16:54,767 --> 00:16:56,400
- Red!
- Don't you dare! Red!

317
00:16:56,467 --> 00:16:57,433
Red!

318
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:01,833
Mom, I didn't mean to hurt you.

319
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:04,133
- No, no, no!
- I'm sorry.

320
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,633
- Mom!
- Don't come near me!

321
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:08,067
Yen!

322
00:17:08,133 --> 00:17:09,367
- Yen!
- Mom!

323
00:17:09,433 --> 00:17:10,400
Yen!

324
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,867
Mom, let's talk.

325
00:17:23,900 --> 00:17:26,167
Let's fix this.

326
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:27,633
We don't need to talk.

327
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,367
Because you don't need me
anymore.

328
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:35,733
Mom, that's not true.

329
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,133
You chose him.

330
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:42,367
He's your priority now
and your future child.

331
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:52,933
Now I know that I don't have
a place in your life.

332
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:57,133
Mom, that's not true.

333
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,667
Don't talk like that.

334
00:17:58,733 --> 00:18:01,300
We can still fix this.

335
00:18:01,367 --> 00:18:04,133
What are we going to fix?

336
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:07,767
You ruined everything!

337
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:12,900
Of all the people to love...

338
00:18:17,633 --> 00:18:21,633
Why does it have to be the son
of the woman who put me in jail!

339
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:23,167
Why does it have to be the child
of the person...

340
00:18:23,267 --> 00:18:27,367
- Mom, please stop.
- who made my life miserable!

341
00:18:27,433 --> 00:18:29,733
What else is left to talk about?

342
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:33,933
- What do we need to talk about?
- Miss Amanda...

343
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,767
Miss Amanda, I know you can't
accept our relationship, okay?

344
00:18:38,967 --> 00:18:40,933
But I won't abandon
your daughter

345
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:43,000
and our future child together.

346
00:18:43,067 --> 00:18:46,800
Just please, give us a chance
to fix everything.

347
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:49,000
I don't want the two of you
to fight either!

348
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:53,667
You have the nerve
to tell me that!

349
00:18:53,733 --> 00:18:54,733
Mom!

350
00:18:56,933 --> 00:19:00,900
You are the reason
we're fighting!

351
00:19:00,967 --> 00:19:02,133
Your mom!

352
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:04,800
Your whole family!

353
00:19:04,867 --> 00:19:08,067
You make our life miserable!

354
00:19:08,133 --> 00:19:10,533
Why can't you just leave us
in peace!

355
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:13,133
Why can't you leave us alone!

356
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:16,100
Why do you have to come
into our life!

357
00:19:16,167 --> 00:19:18,200
-Go ahead, Miss Amanda! Hurt me!
-Why do you have to come

358
00:19:18,267 --> 00:19:20,933
- into our life!
- Mom, please stop!

359
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:23,700
- What's going on?
- Amanda's here!

360
00:19:23,767 --> 00:19:24,833
She's talking to Eden.

361
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,433
- Hurt me!
- You're the reason

362
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:32,767
we're fighting!

363
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:34,567
Hurt me! I will take it!

364
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:36,400
- Oh, really?
- I will take it all!

365
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:38,400
- That's enough!
- I will take it all!

366
00:19:38,467 --> 00:19:39,867
But I won't say sorry
for loving your daughter!

367
00:19:39,933 --> 00:19:41,267
Let go of my son!

368
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:42,400
Stop it! Stop it!

369
00:19:42,467 --> 00:19:44,300
You don't have the right
to hurt my son!

370
00:19:44,367 --> 00:19:46,067
Why can't I hurt him?

371
00:19:46,133 --> 00:19:48,267
He got my daughter pregnant!

372
00:19:57,133 --> 00:20:00,600
-Mom, stop.
-Don't you dare to come near me!

373
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:04,033
Stay right there!
Stay with those people!

374
00:20:05,267 --> 00:20:06,300
No, Mom!

375
00:20:07,433 --> 00:20:09,000
I won't leave you, Mom.

376
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:13,133
There are a lot of men out there
that you can love!

377
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:16,133
Why do you have to fall
for the son of these monsters!

378
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:18,300
What?

379
00:20:19,633 --> 00:20:23,000
You don't know
how much you hurt me.

380
00:20:24,067 --> 00:20:26,367
You should have just killed me!

381
00:20:27,933 --> 00:20:29,833
Mom, I'm sorry.

382
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:31,233
Mom.

383
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,967
I didn't mean to do this to you.

384
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:34,600
I didn't know.

385
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:39,533
Shut up! It hurts to think
that I don't matter to you!

386
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,600
It hurts to think...

387
00:20:45,233 --> 00:20:52,100
that you love that guy
more than me!

388
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:58,700
You've hurt me so much!

389
00:20:58,767 --> 00:20:59,867
Did you know

390
00:21:01,567 --> 00:21:04,167
you're the only reason
I'm alive?

391
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:09,167
You're my only source
of strength.

392
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:12,567
But you took away
my reason to live...

393
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:17,800
because of what you did.

394
00:21:20,567 --> 00:21:22,400
Mom...

395
00:21:22,467 --> 00:21:23,600
I'm tired.

396
00:21:26,767 --> 00:21:30,667
This is worse than the time
your father left me.

397
00:21:33,767 --> 00:21:36,067
If only I knew you would do
this to me,

398
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:39,600
I would have just let myself
rot in jail.

399
00:21:39,667 --> 00:21:42,367
I wish I'd died in jail!

400
00:21:45,567 --> 00:21:46,967
- Mom...
-If only I knew

401
00:21:47,033 --> 00:21:48,533
you would do this to me,

402
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:51,600
I would have just stayed
in jail!

403
00:21:51,667 --> 00:21:55,600
That way, I wouldn't have to go
through all this pain.

404
00:21:57,100 --> 00:21:59,700
Mom, I didn't mean to hurt you.

405
00:22:01,033 --> 00:22:03,100
Mom, I need you!

406
00:22:03,167 --> 00:22:04,467
- Mom, don't leave me.
- Amanda.

407
00:22:04,533 --> 00:22:05,800
- Amanda.
- Mom!

408
00:22:05,867 --> 00:22:07,167
Yenyen!

409
00:22:07,233 --> 00:22:09,500
- Yenyen!
- Yen!

410
00:22:09,567 --> 00:22:11,800
- Red! Red!
- Yen.

411
00:22:11,867 --> 00:22:13,767
- Red.
- Auntie.

412
00:22:16,733 --> 00:22:18,167
I'm sorry, Yen. I'm sorry.

413
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:26,367
In this situation,
Amanda's on the losing end.

414
00:22:26,433 --> 00:22:28,100
Because it's her daughter
who got pregnant.

415
00:22:28,167 --> 00:22:30,167
And it's even more painful

416
00:22:30,233 --> 00:22:34,233
because your son
is the baby's father.

417
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:36,400
I don't care about
what other people would say.

418
00:22:36,467 --> 00:22:38,533
All I care about is you.

419
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:40,867
We survived a plane crash,
remember?

420
00:22:40,933 --> 00:22:43,667
And we've been through a lot
on the island.

421
00:22:43,733 --> 00:22:46,233
And yet we're still standing.

422
00:22:46,300 --> 00:22:47,567
We can survive this.

423
00:22:47,633 --> 00:22:50,100
Eden didn't know
that Rina was Red's mother

424
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:53,067
when they were on the island.

425
00:22:53,133 --> 00:22:56,133
She didn't ask to be with Red.

426
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,833
You won't understand me

427
00:22:57,900 --> 00:23:00,667
because you weren't
in my position.

428
00:23:00,733 --> 00:23:03,500
And you don't know how it feels

429
00:23:03,567 --> 00:23:06,467
to get betrayed
by your daughter.

430
00:23:06,533 --> 00:23:07,667
Please, just leave

431
00:23:07,733 --> 00:23:10,067
if you're here
to cause a problem.

432
00:23:10,133 --> 00:23:14,767
I came here
because I've made a decision.
